# ansible/roles/jellyfin/templates/jellyfin.container.j2
# Podman Quadlet — Jellyfin Media Server
# Config: local SSD  |  Media: SMB mount from Bevbot 1.0 NAS
# Managed by Ansible — do not edit manually.

[Unit]
Description=Jellyfin Media Server
After=network-online.target mnt-bevbot_media.mount
# Wait for the SMB mount before starting Jellyfin
Requires=mnt-bevbot_media.mount

[Container]
Image=docker.io/jellyfin/jellyfin:latest
ContainerName=jellyfin
Network=bevbot_net

# Config and cache stay on local NVMe — fast and persistent
Volume={{ jellyfin_config_dir }}:/config:z
Volume={{ jellyfin_cache_dir }}:/cache:z

# Media is served from Bevbot 1.0 over SMB
Volume={{ jellyfin_media_mount }}:/media:ro,z

# Timezone
Volume=/etc/localtime:/etc/localtime:ro
Environment=TZ=America/Denver

# Ports
PublishPort={{ jellyfin_port }}:8096
PublishPort={{ jellyfin_https_port }}:8920
PublishPort=1900:1900/udp
PublishPort=7359:7359/udp

# NVIDIA GPU passthrough via CDI (Blackwell RTX PRO 500)
# Comment out if you want CPU-only transcoding
AddDevice=nvidia.com/gpu=all

# Security options
SecurityLabelDisable=false
NoNewPrivileges=true

Label=io.containers.autoupdate=registry

[Service]
Restart=always
RestartSec=15
TimeoutStartSec=120

[Install]
WantedBy=default.target
